Prim's Algorithm

Prim's Algorithm is a recursive algorithm that generates all possible permutations of a given set of elements, starting from the first element and working backwards. The basic steps involved are as follows:

  • Choose an initial value for the first element.
  • For each subsequent element, generate all possible permutations using Prim's Algorithm.
  • Return the final sequence of permutations.
